# Turma native agent configuration.
#
# Plain KEY=value (no `export`, no shell expansion, no $HOME in values). Loaded
# both by systemd (EnvironmentFile) and by the launcher (`set -a; . file`). The
# launcher fills HOME-relative defaults for any key left BLANK, which is the
# recommended way to set the paths — don't hardcode /home/<you> here.
#
# install.sh writes this once and never overwrites it, so your edits survive
# reinstalls and updates.

# --- Required -------------------------------------------------------------
# Hub base URL. The agent connects purely OUTBOUND, so this is the public
# Cloudflare-tunnel URL (works from any network).
TURMA_URL=https://turma.example.com
# Shared bearer token — must equal the hub's TURMA_AGENT_TOKEN. Also used as the
# per-session ttyd basic-auth password. Keep this file private (chmod 600).
TURMA_TOKEN=
# Host key the hub identifies this agent by. install.sh seeds $(hostname).
DEVICE_NAME=

# --- Paths (leave BLANK to accept the launcher's HOME-relative defaults) ---
# Git root scanned one level deep for repos; worktrees live under it. Default: $HOME/git
REPOS_ROOT=
# Where Claude Code keeps transcripts. Default: $HOME/.claude/projects
# (MUST NOT be /root/.claude/projects on a native install.)
CLAUDE_PROJECTS_ROOT=

# --- Tuning (code defaults shown) -----------------------------------------
MAX_SESSIONS=6
TTYD_PORT_BASE=7700
TURMA_INTERVAL=20

# --- Auto-update (optional) -----------------------------------------------
# Override the release source or cadence if needed.
# TURMA_REPO=xerktech/turma
# TURMA_UPDATE_INTERVAL=3600
# GH_TOKEN=            # only if `gh` isn't logged in on this host

# --- Optional integrations ------------------------------------------------
# GH_CLONE_OWNERS=              # extra owners the hub may clone from (space/comma)
# A host polls ONE ticket source. Jira Cloud:
# JIRA_SITE=                    # your-org.atlassian.net
# JIRA_EMAIL=
# JIRA_TOKEN=
# ...or Azure DevOps (self-hosted or Services); AZDO_* wins if both are set:
# AZDO_URL=                     # https://dev.azure.com/org, or a self-hosted
#                               # https://tfs.company.com/tfs/DefaultCollection
# AZDO_TOKEN=                   # PAT with Work Items (Read)
# AZDO_PROJECT=                 # optional: scope to one project (else org-wide)
# AZDO_USER=                    # optional: display-only, for the board's merge field
# AZDO_API_VERSION=6.0          # self-hosted trails cloud: 7.0 = Server 2022,
#                               # 6.0 = 2020, 5.0 = 2019, 4.1 = TFS 2018. An
#                               # out-of-range version is answered with a 400.
# BOARD_ORG_NAME=               # the board's org LABEL, overriding the name
#                               # derived from the site: a self-hosted collection
#                               # derives to "defaultcollection", its deployment
#                               # detail rather than the org. Presentational only
#                               # — the siteKey routing and the hub's ledgers key
#                               # on is untouched, so this is safe to change later.
